                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <ListLevel>1</ListLevel>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>3. </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>BENEFICIARY</Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Bold</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>: The party receiving the benefits should the Principal not comply with the requirements of the Agreement the beneficiary is always the City of Knoxville. </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <ListLevel>1</ListLevel>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value />
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>The Performance and Indemnity Agreement is the City’s assurance that it will be reimbursed for assuming the costs of work not completed by the Principal according to required specifications and approved plans. The City plans reviewer will determine the dollar amount of the guarantee based on the actual construction and/or potential remediation expenses, using guidelines in the Stormwater and Street Ordinance.</Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value />
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>When the reviewing engineer determines that a Performance and Indemnity Agreement is required for a project, the party submitting the plans will be notified.  It is that party’s responsibility (and/or the Principal’s responsibility) to provide Stormwater Engineering with the following information: </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value />
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>1. Name, address, phone and fax numbers and the contact person for the Principal </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <ListLevel>1</ListLevel>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>2. The form of guarantee </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <ListLevel>1</ListLevel>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>3. Name, address, phone and fax numbers and the contact person for the guarantor </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <ListLevel>1</ListLevel>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value />
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>Upon receipt of this information, Stormwater Engineering will prepare the Agreement for execution.  When the document has been fully executed, it is to be returned to Stormwater Engineering with the original signatures and notary seals and the original form of guarantee. The initial Performance and Indemnity Agreement covers a one-year time period.  If the project is not completed according to the approved site plans and the city’s standards within that year, the Agreement must be extended.</Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
            </Paragraphs>
            <rd:DefaultName>Textbox18</rd:DefaultName>
            <Top>0.99528in</Top>
            <Left>0.02694in</Left>
            <Height>7.50694in</Height>
            <Width>6.7236in</Width>
            <ZIndex>3</ZIndex>
            <Style>
              <Border>
                <Style>None</Style>
              </Border>
              <PaddingLeft>2pt</PaddingLeft>
              <PaddingRight>2pt</PaddingRight>
              <PaddingTop>2pt</PaddingTop>
              <PaddingBottom>2pt</PaddingBottom>
            </Style>
          </Textbox>
          <Textbox Name="Textbox1">
            <CanGrow>true</CanGrow>
            <KeepTogether>true</KeepTogether>
            <Paragraphs>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>Approximately 60 days prior to the expiration date, the Principal and the Guarantor will be notified. The letter contains the names of contact persons within Stormwater Engineering to contact for either an extension or a release. It is the Principal’s responsibility to contact Stormwater Engineering to request that the Agreement be released or extended. A second letter is issued approximately 21 days prior to expiration, if needed. </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value />
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>If the Principal feels that the project is complete, he must request that a city construction inspector visit the site to determine if all requirements have been met.  Basic general requirements for the release of an Agreement are: </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value />
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>1. Development certification for constructed items being bonded (including accurate as-built plans) </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <ListLevel>1</ListLevel>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>2. No erosion problems, structural deficiencies, unsafe conditions or maintenance issues </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <ListLevel>1</ListLevel>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>3. A good stand of grass within required areas </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <ListLevel>1</ListLevel>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value />
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>There may be other specific requirements for each project. After the inspection, the Principal will be notified whether all requirements have been met and the Performance and Indemnity Agreement can be considered for release or if it must be extended. </Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value />
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
              <Paragraph>
                <TextRuns>
                  <TextRun>
                    <Value>If an extension is required, the Principal must submit the executed Extension of Performance and Indemnity Agreement, along with either an amended Letter of Credit or an extension of the surety bond. If the extension documents have not been received in the Engineering Department ten days prior to expiration, collection procedures may be implemented.</Value>
                    <Style>
                      <FontStyle>Normal</FontStyle>
                      <FontFamily>Times New Roman</FontFamily>
                      <FontSize>12pt</FontSize>
                      <FontWeight>Normal</FontWeight>
                      <TextDecoration>None</TextDecoration>
                      <Color>#000000</Color>
                    </Style>
                  </TextRun>
                </TextRuns>
                <Style />
              </Paragraph>
            </Paragraphs>
            <rd:DefaultName>Textbox1</rd:DefaultName>
            <Top>8.61333in</Top>
            <Height>4.42709in</Height>
            <Width>6.68929in</Width>
            <ZIndex>4</ZIndex>
